A ```JavaMailSender``` bean is automatically configured in this service
which is the standard way of sending e-mails in Spring.

To use it in a service, you can simply inject it like this:

```java
class MyService implements IMyService {
    private final JavaMailSender mailSender;

    public MyService(JavaMailSender mailSender) {
        this.mailSender = mailSender;
    }

    public void sendEmail(string recipient) {
        SimpleMailMessage message = new SimpleMailMessage();
        message.setFrom("someone@somewhere.com");
        message.setTo(recipient);
        message.setSubject("Hello");
        message.setText("Hello, this is a test e-mail");
        mailSender.send(message);
    }
}

```


